chinese: 我那会儿不能见他们.我要出庭.
english: I can't meet them then. I'm in court.

chinese: 你在那之后第二天才出庭.
english: You're in court the next day.

chinese: 是的.
english: Right.

chinese: 但我周三也要出庭.
english: But I'm also in court on Wednesday.

chinese: 第二天就是周三.
english: The next day is Wednesday.

chinese: Trish,我们才刚开始就已经节奏不同了.
english: Trish, we just started and we're already out of sync.

chinese: 我不能参加所有会议.
english: I cannot have all these meetings.

chinese: 白天没那么多时间.
english: There aren't enough hours in the day.

chinese: 恕我直言,
english: With all due respect,

chinese: 你不把事情写在日程表上.
english: you don't write things down in the calendar.

chinese: 所以我不知道你的安排究竟有多满,
english: So I don't know how full your schedule is,

chinese: 这就是我们还会有这些小会的原因.
english: which is why we still have these little meetings.

chinese: 我们是否能一致同意周三之后是周四呢?
english: Can we agree that the day after Wednesday is Thursday?

chinese: 开个玩笑,Trish.一个小玩笑.
english: That's a joke, Trish. A little joke.

chinese: 我们可以从头开始吗?
english: May we start from the beginning?

chinese: 当然可以.
english: By all means.

chinese: 信用卡协会想在周二上午见你.
english: The Credit Card Association would like to meet with you on Tuesday morning.

chinese: 好的.可以在早上进行.
english: Fine. I can do it in the morning.

chinese: 然后我要出庭.
english: Afterwards, I'm in court.

chinese: 好的.哪个案子?
english: Fine. Which case?

chinese: 公众对Kenton.
english: People vs Kenton.

chinese: 这案子要到下周才开始.
english: That case doesn't start until next week!

chinese: 我们谈的就是下周的安排!
english: We're talking about next week!

chinese: 我们谈的是本周的安排!
english: We're talking about this week!

chinese: Trish,我说了,"让我们谈下周的安排."
english: Trish, I said, "Let's talk about next week."

chinese: 你是在上周五说的.
english: You said it on Friday.

chinese: 上周说的"下周"到这周就变成"这周"了.
english: Last week, "next week" means "this week" this week.

chinese: 你会成为一名出色的律师.
english: You're going to make a very good attorney.
